!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

brisk /brɪsk/

(brisker,briskest) 

1. ADJ A brisk activity or action is done quickly and in an energetic way. 轻快的 

例： Taking a brisk walk can often induce a feeling of well-being. 轻快的散步经常能使人心旷神怡。 

2. briskly ADV 轻快地 [ADV with v] 

例： Eve walked briskly down the corridor to her son's room. 伊芙轻快地沿着走廊走到她儿子的房间。 

3. ADJ If trade or business is brisk , things are being sold very quickly and a lot of money is being made. (买卖、生意) 兴隆的 

例： Vendors were doing a brisk trade in souvenirs. 小贩们的纪念品生意很兴隆。 

4. briskly ADV 兴隆地 [ADV after v] 

例： A trader said gold sold briskly on the local market. 一位贸易商说黄金在当地市场的销售很兴旺。 

5. ADJ If the weather is brisk , it is cold and fresh. 寒冷而清新的 

例： ...a typically brisk winter's day on the south coast. …南海岸典型的寒冷而清新的冬日。 

6. ADJ Someone who is brisk behaves in a busy, confident way which shows that they want to get things done quickly. 干脆利索的 

例： The Chief summoned me downstairs. He was brisk and businesslike. 上司召我到楼下。他做事干脆利索而有效率。 

7. briskly ADV 脆利索地 [ADV with v] 

例： 'Anyhow,' she added briskly, 'it's none of my business.' “无论如何”，她干脆利索地加了一句：“这不关我的事。”

